cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the capacity and degrees of freedom of a two-way relay network, which involves information theory and network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). It also involves network communication, which makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also discusses caching, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper involves some mathematical analysis, which is related to cs.MM (Mathematical Methods).
